properties.sfomuseum:description: Flight information packet issued by American Airlines, comprising:a. folder titled “Flagship Information / America’s Leading Airline” with full color photographic image on front and rear cover depicting three male pilots and two female flight attendants standing on airfield in front of grounded aircraft; tri-fold format with three pockets containing inserts b-lb. airmail courtesy label; blue and red with “AA” eagle logo and text, “Air Mail / American Airlines”c. airmail courtesy label; blue and red with “AA” eagle logo and text, “Air Mail / American Airlines”;d. airmail courtesy label; blue and red with “AA” eagle logo and text, “Air Mail / American Airlines”e. circular luggage label; orange, blue, and white with airline servicemarkf. circular luggage label; orange, blue, and white with airline servicemarkg. postcard depicting full color photographic image of passengers deplaning from aircraft “Flagship Boston” on airfieldh. inflight information pamphlet titled “Welcome aboard / American Airlines” depicting color illustration of smiling female flight attendant in blue uniform and hat; multipage bookleti. brochure promoting car rental with Hertz; yellow cover with black and white illustration of people walking toward a car; tri-fold formatj. comment card; blue and red cover; bi-fold formatk. timetable effective March 1, 1953; folded multipage bookletl. system route map full color illustration of woman and two children ascending ramp stairs, waving toward viewer
properties.wof:name: flight information packet: American Airlines
